The band released their first demo "Blueprint of Reconstruction" in 2008.[citation needed] The band consists of vocalist Kenta Koie, guitarist Kazuki Takemura, Hiroki Ikegawa on bass guitar, drummer Tatsuya Amano and Terufumi Tamano on keyboards.

They then released their first studio album "The Artificial Theory for the Dramatic Beauty" through Zestone Records in 2009[citation needed], and their second studio album "The Dream, The Space" in 2011 through Tragic Hero Records. Crossfaith then released their second EP "Zion" in September 2012, this acted as a promotional release to countries outside of Japan.
